Build succeeds with zero errors and zero warnings. Here's the summary of the fix:

**In MSTest v4, `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj, out var t)` was replaced with a return-value pattern:**

```csharp
// v3 (old)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor, out var typed);

// v4 (new)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor);
```

The method now returns the casted value directly instead of using an `out` parameter. The assertion behavior (fail if not the right type) is unchanged. I updated all three call sites and bumped the MSTest package to 4.1.0 â€” the project builds cleanly.
